        Grandma :-</font><br>
        <font color="#663366" face="Comic Sans MS"><font size="+1">&nbsp; </font><b><font size="+2">Droupadi
        Vaidya</font></b></font><br>
        <font size="+1" face="Comic Sans MS" color="#000000">With Love and
        affection we call her &quot;Amaji&quot;. A Hindi school teacher and
        sports coordinator of Senior Secondary School Mandi, she has long list
        of credits in her pot. She is now an active social worker and is working
        hard for the up-liftment of women in Himachal Pradesh. She even got a
        State Award for this last year. One thing which I will always remember
        about her is never shirk responsibilities and be brave and have trust in
        GOD. A religious lady of late seventies can still walk several miles
        without getting tired and can do numerous tasks of home along with the
        social work. Her students today are the senior bureaucrats in Himachal
        Pradesh and they all respect her a lot and thank her what she has made
        them. She has an aura of her own. I am glad to have her as my grandma
        and I love and respect her a lot.</font></p>
